{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Bundles up pointers to each of the matching substrings from a match"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and stores them in an array of gchar pointers. The first element in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the returned array is the match number 0, i.e. the entire matched","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"text."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoProtocol\/fetchAll()"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fetchAll","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a sub pattern didn’t match anything (e.g. sub pattern 1, matching","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“b” against “(a)?b”) then an empty string is inserted.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the last match was obtained using the DFA algorithm, that is using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_regex_match_all()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_regex_match_all_full()"},{"text":", the retrieved","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strings are not that matched by sets of parentheses but that of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"matched substring. Substrings are matched in reverse order of length,"